<p><strong>Q: Who is Sheila Fitzpatrick?</strong>
A: Sheila Fitzpatrick is a renowned British-Australian historian specializing in Russian history. She is an emeritus professor at the University of Chicago and the University of Sydney, known for her groundbreaking work on the Russian Revolution, everyday life in the Soviet Union, and cultural history.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What is the significance of Sheila Fitzpatrick's work on the Russian Revolution?</strong>
A: Fitzpatrick's book "The Russian Revolution: A New History" (1994) is widely considered a classic in the field. It provides a comprehensive and nuanced account of the Revolution, challenging traditional narratives and offering fresh perspectives on its social and political dynamics.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Where can I find Sheila Fitzpatrick's "The Russian Revolution: A New History" in PDF format?</strong>
A: You can find a PDF version of Sheila Fitzpatrick's "The Russian Revolution: A New History" on various online platforms, including:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://scholar.google.com/books?id=7Kn2Bd9467oC&amp;pg=PA1">Google Scholar</a></li>
