<p><strong>Q: What are some of the key arguments and insights presented in Fitzpatrick's book?</strong>
A: Fitzpatrick's book argues that the Russian Revolution was not simply a Marxist-Leninist takeover but a complex process involving multiple social groups and ideologies. She emphasizes the role of popular protest, peasant discontent, and cultural factors in shaping the Revolution's course.</p>
<p><strong>Q: How can I access other works by Sheila Fitzpatrick?</strong>
A: In addition to "The Russian Revolution: A New History," Fitzpatrick has published numerous other books and articles on Russian history. You can find her publications through online library catalogs, academic databases, and her personal website: <a href="https://sheilafitzpatrick.net/">https://sheilafitzpatrick.net/</a>.</p>